A 27-year-old man is expected in court on Monday after he was arrested by Msobomvu police for possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition."The suspect was arrested during the night of Friday, at Mchubakazi Township, Butterworth," described police spokesperson, Captain jackson Manatha."He was arrested during stop and search operation. "The firearm - namely a pistol, will be sent for ballistic test to establish if it was not used in the commission of crime around Butterworth."He said that the suspect will appear before the Butterworth Magistrate's Court on Monday on charges of possession of unlicensed fire arm and ammunition.